Media Query
Definition
-> A Media Query is used to make a website responsive.
 It applies CSS rules based on screen size or device type.
It is mainly used for mobile-friendly design.

Basic Syntax
@media (max-width: 600px) {
 /* CSS rules here */
}

Meaning:
If the screen width is 600px or less, apply these styles.
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>

 <style>
   p {
     background-color: black;
     color: white;
   }

   @media (max-width: 600px) {
     p {
       background-color: green;
     }
   }
 </style>
</head>
<body>

 <p>Responsive Text</p>

</body>
</html>

Normal screen → Black
Small screen → Green
